SIMPLE: submerge
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Submerge
<hw>Sub*merge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Submerged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Submerging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>submergere</ets>, <ets>submersum</ets>; <ets>sub</ets> under +
<ets>mergere</ets> to plunge: cf. F. <ets>submerger</ets>. See
<er>Merge</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put under water; to
plunge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cover or overflow with water; to inundate; to
flood; to drown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would thou didst,⟦br⟧
So half my Egypt were <qex>submerged</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1435 --></p>

<p><ent>Submerge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Submerge
<hw>Sub*merge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To plunge into
water or other fluid; to be buried or covered, as by a fluid; to be
merged; hence, to be completely included.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some say swallows <qex>submerge</qex> in ponds.</q> <rj><qau>Gent.
Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Submergence</ent>⟦br⟧
